C3N4/B-C-dots show a larger value for the reaction rate constant (kapp
                        ) than C3N4 and C3N4/C-dots, which means a more effective photocatalytic activity (Fig. 7(d) and (e)). Table S2 summaries the kapp
                         of the as-prepared photocatalysts for the degradation of Rh B and TC. For the degradation of Rh B, the reaction rate constant (kapp
                        ) of C3N4 and C3N4/C-dots was about 4.93 × 10−3 and 7.42 × 10−3 min−1, respectively (Fig. 7(d)). Meanwhile, the corresponding kapp
                         value of C3N4/B-C-dots-0.4 was determined to be 3.56 × 10−2 min−1. The photocatalytic ability of the C3N4/B-C-dots is greatly enhanced and can be almost 4.80 times faster after doping of B element compared to that of C3N4/C-dots. In the case of degradation of TC, the reaction rate constant (kapp
                        ) of C3N4 and C3N4/C-dots was about 3.49 × 10−3 and 5.26 × 10−3 min−1, respectively. The corresponding kapp
                         values of C3N4/B-C-dots-0.4 was determined to be 2.29 × 10−2 min−1. The photocatalytic rate of C3N4/B-C-dots-0.4 was about 4.35-fold C3N4/C-dots. The kapp
                         of the as-prepared photocatalysts agreed well with their photo decolorization curves plotted in Fig. 7(b) and (c).
